{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Commit Message Generator",
  "description": "Automatically generates descriptive commit messages with emojis based on the changes made to files in the repository",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered",
    "patterns": [
      "src/**/*",
      "convex/**/*",
      "components.json",
      "package.json",
      "README.md",
      "*.config.js",
      "*.config.ts"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Make sure to not to make any changes to the file while doing this. you only have to read what has been done\n\nAnalyze the file changes and generate a commit message that:\n\n1. Always starts with \"feat/changes:\" \n2. Uses descriptive emojis for each change (like 🗑️ for removals, 🫟 for additions, 🥪 for UI/UX improvements, etc.)\n3. Describes what was changed in natural, descriptive language\n4. Groups related changes together\n5. Follows this format:\n\nfeat/changes:\n🗑️ Remove the restaurant context and store restaurant data in the local storage \n🫟 Add shadcn config \n🥪 Toast message on success/error\n\nMake sure each line describes a specific change and uses appropriate emojis that match the type of change made. Be descriptive and natural in the language used."
  }
}